Algorithm BinarySearch(arr, target)
Pre: arr is a sorted array
Post: return index if found, else return -1

1. start = 0
2. end = length(arr)-1
3. while start <= end do
       mid = start + (end - start) / 2
       if arr[mid] = target then
            return mid
       else if target < arr[mid] then
            end = mid - 1
       else
            start = mid + 1
4. return -1
End Algorithm


(II)
Algorithm BinarySearch(arr, target)
Pre: arr is sorted in ascending order
Post: returns the index of target if found, else returns -1

start = 0
end = length(arr) - 1

While start <= end do
    mid = start + (end - start) / 2    // Middle element

    If arr[mid] = target then
        Return mid    // Found the element
    Else If target < arr[mid] then
        end = mid - 1    // Look in left half
    Else
        start = mid + 1  // Look in right half
    End If
End While

Return -1   // Element not found
End Algorithm


(III)
Algorithm BinarySearch(arr, target)
Pre: arr is a sorted array
Post: return index if found, else return -1

Step 1: Set start = 0
Step 2: Set end = length(arr) - 1
Step 3: While start <= end do
         Step 3.1: mid = start + (end - start)/2
         Step 3.2: If arr[mid] = target, return mid
         Step 3.3: Else if target < arr[mid], set end = mid - 1
         Step 3.4: Else, set start = mid + 1
Step 4: If not found, return -1
End Algorithm